- `c494764d feat: preview doctor log cleanup via elixir`\n\nValidated each slice:\n- `npx tsc --noEmit`\n- targeted Vitest\n- `npm run b‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"continue","timestamp":"2026-06-26T20:40:12.044Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvfb68h_896581da3572":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvfb68h_896581da3572","importance":5,"narrative":"continue | Done. Pushed final doc cleanup.\n\nLatest pushed:\n- `774a3e0a docs: clarify legacy metrics filters`\n\nBroad audit result: PASS.\n- No blockers found.\n- Remaining guarded paths are destructive or explicitly legacy-only:\n  - mutating `run`, `stop`, `reset`, `merge`, `worktree clean`, purge, doctor `--fix`\n  - legacy-only `daemon`, `run task`, `sling`, `pr`, bare `plan`, sentinel run/start/st‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"continue","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:08:37.815Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvfrjjn_22c1ec2eeb59":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvfrjjn_22c1ec2eeb59","importance":5,"narrative":"continue | Continued audit.\n\nResult:\n- Broad parity audit already PASS.\n- Remaining guarded surfaces are intended:\n  - destructive/mutating legacy paths\n  - legacy-only integrations/workflows\n  - metrics cost filters requiring legacy task store\n\nNo next safe parity slice found.\nCleaned recurring `data/stream_store/*` noise.\n\nRepo state:\n- `dev` == `origin/dev`\n- working tree clean.","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"continue","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:21:21.567Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvfuf95_4cb76102b579":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvfuf95_4cb76102b579","importance":5,"narrative":"how do we 'test' this? | Test in 4 layers.\n\n### 1. Static/build gate\n\n```bash\ngit status --short\nnpx tsc --noEmit\nnpm run build\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n### 2. Targeted unit/subprocess tests\n\nRun all parity-related tests:\n\n```bash\nnpx vitest run -c vitest.unit.config.ts \\\n  src/cli/__tests__/elixir-legacy-guards.test.ts \\\n  src/cli/__tests__/stop.test.ts \\\n  src/cli/__tests__/worktree.test.ts \\\n  sr‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"how do we 'test' this?","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:23:35.984Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqvgcfqt_c290a2bd56fc":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqvgcfqt_c290a2bd56fc","importance":5,"narrative":"/loop until all tests pass without errors | Loop complete. All CI tests pass.\n\nRan:\n- `npm run test:ci` ‚úÖ\n  - unit: 302 files, 4107 tests pass\n  - integration: 38 files, 599 tests pass\n  - e2e smoke: pass\n  - e2e full-run: pass\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` ‚úÖ\n- `npm run build` ‚úÖ\n- `git diff --check` ‚úÖ\n\nFixes pushed:\n- `a57349a0 test: stabilize legacy backend suites`\n\nRepo clean:\n- `dev` == `origin/dev`\n- ‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"/loop until all tests pass without errors","timestamp":"2026-06-26T21:37:36.420Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwftr70_0e01fb5b586f":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwftr70_0e01fb5b586f","importance":5,"narrative":"what's next for testing? | Next testing tiers:\n\n1. **Manual Elixir smoke**\n   - Start server:\n     - `foreman server start`\n   - Run:\n     - `foreman status`\n     - `foreman runs`\n     - `foreman metrics`\n     - `foreman metrics --compact`\n     - `foreman worktree list`\n     - `foreman worktree clean --dry-run`\n     - `foreman stop --list`\n     - `foreman stop --dry-run`\n     - `foreman run --dry‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"what's next for testing?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:10:50.982Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwfxqhc_da68ee15e155":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwfxqhc_da68ee15e155","importance":5,"narrative":"foreman doctor dumps json?  Should we have a --raw/json flag that shows this but have a more human friendly output as the default? | Yes.\n\nCurrent state:\n- `foreman doctor --json` already exists.\n- But default Elixir path still prints:\n  - `Elixir server doctor: PASS`\n  - then raw JSON body\n- That‚Äôs bad default UX.\n\nBetter contract:\n- `foreman doctor` = human summary, default.\n- `foreman doctor -‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"foreman doctor dumps json?  Should we have a --raw/json flag that shows this but have a more human friendly output as t‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:13:56.663Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwg3cuc_46f9f38bd96b":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwg3cuc_46f9f38bd96b","importance":5,"narrative":"do it? | Done + pushed.\n\nCommit:\n- `d5a07f9b feat: render elixir doctor summary`\n\nChanged:\n- `foreman doctor` default Elixir output now human summary.\n- Added `foreman doctor --raw`.\n- `--json` still emits machine-readable JSON.\n- Docs updated.\n\nValidated:\n- `npm run test:unit -- src/cli/commands/__tests__/doctor-elixir.test.ts`\n- `npx tsc --noEmit`\n- `npm run build`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nRepo cl‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"do it?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:18:18.926Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwg5810_6239c7c64701":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwg5810_6239c7c64701","importance":5,"narrative":"foreman doctor lists 'provider adaptors' and 'integrations'.  What are these used for? | They‚Äôre Elixir backend health checks for two extension boundaries.\n\n- **Provider adapters**\n  - Worker execution backends.\n  - Today: mainly `pi_sdk`.\n  - Used when Elixir starts a worker phase via `WorkerProtocol.start_phase(...)`.\n  - Validates:\n    - requested provider exists\n    - provider is production-r‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"foreman doctor lists 'provider adaptors' and 'integrations'.  What are these used for?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:19:46.012Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwg7bp3_5aff1865ced8":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwg7bp3_5aff1865ced8","importance":5,"narrative":"give me a use case for integrations?  I get what adapters do? | Use case: **Jira ticket becomes Foreman task, once.**\n\nFlow:\n1. Jira webhook fires: issue moved to `Ready for Dev`.\n2. Integration sends command to Foreman:\n   - ‚Äúcreate task for Jira issue PROJ-123‚Äù\n   - includes dedupe key: `jira:PROJ-123:ready-for-dev`\n3. Elixir records event:\n   - `IntegrationCommandIngested`\n4. Projection stores‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"give me a use case for integrations?  I get what adapters do?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:21:24.084Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwg8g5l_bc20256ff666":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwg8g5l_bc20256ff666","importance":5,"narrative":"Ah, so in the case of Jira do task updates get written back to Jira? | Planned/partial, not full native loop yet.\n\nCurrent intent:\n- Jira can be an external task source/status surface.\n- Foreman should ingest Jira events into Elixir, dedupe them, create/link tasks.\n- Foreman should eventually emit updates back:\n  - task status changes\n  - run started/completed/failed\n  - comments with report link‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"Ah, so in the case of Jira do task updates get written back to Jira?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:22:16.517Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwganjs_480a84014ee6":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwganjs_480a84014ee6","importance":5,"narrative":"Not in beads, use foreman's native tasks | Added native Foreman task.\n\n- ID: `52ba0d80-913d-4880-871b-a81e308c34d4-2c7da`\n- Title: `Add native Jira write-back integration`\n- Status: `backlog`\n- Priority: low\n\nCovers:\n- Jira-linked task status write-back\n- run started/completed/failed comments\n- blocker/needs-operator state sync\n- report/PR links\n- dedupe/audit events\n- native Elixir path, legacy ‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"Not in beads, use foreman's native tasks","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:23:59.411Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwgdobm_0a2158892d0d":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwgdobm_0a2158892d0d","importance":5,"narrative":"can we write E2E tests that test the critical path with foreman?  Instead of manually testing we can reuse these tests going forward? | Yes. Best next move.\n\nAdd reusable **Elixir native critical-path E2E** lane:\n\n```bash\nnpm run test:e2e:elixir\n```\n\nCovers repeatable manual smoke:\n\n1. **Server lifecycle**\n   - temp `HOME`\n   - isolated server port/data dir\n   - `foreman server start`\n   - `forem‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"can we write E2E tests that test the critical path with foreman?  Instead of manually testing we can reuse these tests ‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:26:20.359Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwgfcrx_8b8fdb35eb8a":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwgfcrx_8b8fdb35eb8a","importance":5,"narrative":"how would we execute the e2e tests? | Proposed commands:\n\n```bash\nnpm run test:e2e:elixir\n```\n\nFor all E2E:\n\n```bash\nnpm run test:e2e\n```\n\nUpdate scripts to include:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"test:e2e:smoke\": \"vitest run -c vitest.e2e.smoke.config.ts\",\n  \"test:e2e:full-run\": \"vitest run -c vitest.e2e.full-run.config.ts\",\n  \"test:e2e:elixir\": \"vitest run -c vitest.e2e.elixir.config.ts\",\n  \"test:e2e\": \"npm run‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"how would we execute the e2e tests?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:27:38.710Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwhcy4w_3297c30def24":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwhcy4w_3297c30def24","importance":5,"narrative":"can you build it? | Built + pushed.\n\nCommit:\n- `9ed23352 test: add elixir critical path e2e`\n\nNew command:\n```bash\nnpm run test:e2e:elixir\n```\n\nAlso included in:\n```bash\nnpm run test:e2e\nnpm run test:ci\n```\n\nCovers:\n- isolated Elixir server\n- doctor human/JSON\n- metrics compact\n- project registration\n- task create/approve/list/show\n- scheduler claim\n- runs/status/logs\n- worktree/stop/reset/purge ‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"can you build it?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T14:53:46.048Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwhnk38_c2deecfd9f3c":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwhnk38_c2deecfd9f3c","importance":5,"narrative":"there's literally only one elixir test? | Yep. Bad shape.\n\nFixed: split into 6 Elixir E2E tests in same lane:\n\n- server status + health\n- doctor + metrics\n- task create/approve/list/show\n- scheduler claim\n- read-only operator views\n- fail-closed legacy guards\n\nValidated:\n- `npm run test:e2e:elixir` ‚úÖ ‚Äî now `6 passed`\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` ‚úÖ\n- `git diff --check` ‚úÖ\n\nAmended + pushed:\n- `1d007928 tes‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"there's literally only one elixir test?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:02:01.058Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwhx9n8_c14d9ebf46e5":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwhx9n8_c14d9ebf46e5","importance":5,"narrative":"what exactly is being tested by the elixir tests? | Elixir E2E lane tests one shared isolated Elixir server + temp project.\n\nFile:\n- `src/integration/__tests__/elixir-critical-path.e2e.test.ts`\n\nCommand:\n- `npm run test:e2e:elixir`\n\nTests:\n\n1. **Server health/status**\n   - starts `packages/foreman_server` via `mix run --no-halt`\n   - waits for HTTP health\n   - runs `foreman server status --port 4‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"what exactly is being tested by the elixir tests?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:09:34.073Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwhy6lr_ef3ebb959d8e":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwhy6lr_ef3ebb959d8e","importance":5,"narrative":"what so run is still using node? | Yes ‚Äî **plain `foreman run` is still legacy Node-only** in default Elixir mode.\n\nCurrent contract:\n\n- `foreman run` ‚Üí **blocked/fails closed** in Elixir mode.\n- `foreman run --dry-run` ‚Üí Elixir projection-backed preview.\n- Actual execution path should be:\n  - start Elixir server/scheduler: `foreman server start`\n  - create/approve tasks via native task commands\n‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"what so run is still using node?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:10:16.785Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwi0a32_7a37a51bc58d":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwi0a32_7a37a51bc58d","importance":5,"narrative":"isn't the primary purpose of elixir to use event sourcing?  meaning run would no longer be 'blind' to what the run is doing?? | Yes. Correct.\n\nPrimary Elixir purpose:\n- event-sourced command ingestion\n- projections for task/run/operator state\n- scheduler decisions from projections\n- run lifecycle emitted as events\n- CLI/operator views no longer blind/stale/local-file based\n\nCurrent problem:\n- **E‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"isn't the primary purpose of elixir to use event sourcing?  meaning run would no longer be 'blind' to what the run is d‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:11:54.627Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwi1qm9_8f89644d30c8":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwi1qm9_8f89644d30c8","importance":5,"narrative":"what else is still using the legacy backend? | Yes. Still legacy / Node-gated today:\n\n## Fully legacy-only commands/paths\n\nRequire `FOREMAN_BACKEND=node`:\n\n- `foreman run` actual dispatch\n- `foreman run task ...` direct worker bridge\n- `foreman daemon start|stop|status|restart`\n- `foreman pr`\n- `foreman sling ...`\n- default `foreman plan <description>` PRD‚ÜíTRD pipeline\n  - Elixir alternatives: `f‚Ä¶","sessionId":"2026-06-23T20-36-02-778Z_019ef632-765a-782d-84bf-5d724872473a","subtitle":"what else is still using the legacy backend?","timestamp":"2026-06-27T15:13:02.696Z","title":"conversation","type":"other"},"type":"compressed"},"obs_mqwjdu0l_3a7abff5c88c":{"observation":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwjdu0l_3a7abff5c88c","importance":5,"narrative"